    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5eeb1736_79f23360",
        "filename": "led/job/job.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-18T21:39:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Theoretically you could have a swarming task with the command\n\n   python -c \"print \u0027hi there\u0027\"\n\nWhich would run, but wouldn\u0027t require exe or user payload to be set. It would be weird, but you could do it.\n\nThis particular bit is trying to calculate input properties to pass to the led recipe module. Since \u0027exe\u0027 is 100% related to buildbucket, and UserPayload could have other non-recipe stuff in it, I\u0027ve opted to prefer the exe definition. Practically speaking if you stick to the `led` command line, you can\u0027t have both of these defined at the same time.",
      "parentUuid": "f900e059_29c14f11",
      "revId": "fc72a5818f84ed77a92cd6e517a72bb56c7b9241",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
